The paper discusses the implementation and testing of various Kalman filters and observers for power system dynamic state estimation under model uncertainty and potential cyber attacks. This involves the use of control systems (cs.SY), cybersecurity (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
